I need creating a design strategy/plan/instruction for a frontend developer.

we are building a social media platform and we need to build a demo/poc. its not really meant to be able to provide features needed for the final product and the scope is to get something that looks good, and to show investors, so we need some of the features to work good enough to show the content.


the name of the platform is rewall, i will provide you with the pitch deck. I have a vision for what should be included in the poc and i what you to interview, branstorm and discuss to define the scope and outline the design requiremnts etc


the idea is:

think of it as a reddit, with minimalist design, and a focus on:

 - get research based answers to questions

 - learn new areas

 - find relevant sources

 - alot of initial focuses around research papers


a community, where users can discuss.

rewall has main types of discovery methods, (search and feed) and needs to support these

 - users (individual users with a profile, both for visible but also associated data used by a algorithm)

 - topics (specific areas that can be discussed, its like subreddit, where discussion can take place, etc.)

- sources (like research papers, and here there can be a forum/discussion for this specific source)

- Publisher (a source will always come from a publisher, and a publisher can get verified if they are verified to be unbiased and trustworhy.)

- Groups (users can create a public or private group for anything (like a student project or a niched interesed). the difference from topics will be that the users are more in control and moderate it themselves.


there will be a recommendation algorithm to provide content in the feed. the feed should have a mix of things like:

- interesting topics you might like

- interesting sources you might want to read etc

- new activity/discussion in a forum you are following.

etc


the search bar allows you to ask a question, like an area to learn about, or find a source that can be useful, navigate topics, groups, etc

it can be used both as a search engine, using rewalls ai to help learning och researching a new subject, but also as a classic social media community search.


AI:

rewall uses AI both for a recommendation engine/algorithm, but also help keep track of ontologogical connections in and between research papers. the platform (that we are focusing on now) is a way for people/users to get their infomation in a way that has higher trust than searching online. rewall is a source of infomation, that adjusts to your preferences of recieving it, aswell as a sophisticated social media platform to encourage community around the areas.


Perspective:

one thing that is important is that rewall encorages multiple perspectives. it uses the ai mapping of the sources to understand if there are sources that counter each other, and can therefore provide several countering sources. for topics, we want to encourage multiple different views on a subject and make it easy for a user to learn a subject from multiple different angels and perspectives. this should also be reflected in the ui.


the ui should be a landing page/front page, with a main feed where the content is mixed, with different types of content. then we have a search bar that you can use to look into infomation gathering aspects, get questions to answers and community specific things (like finding groups etc).


you should be able to enter a persons profile, and each profile needs relevant things like that topics they are following, see their recent contributions in discussions/forums/comments etc.

there should be pages for groups and for topics, and then we need the sources to have a pages aswell. initially we are focusing on research papers, so that means that we need like a discussion field below it,




