1. for the poc, im thinking that the perspective aspect should be visible in the topic-screen. the rewell system will use users discussion data together with its AI ontological mapping system to place them in a vector space, that then could be visualize in spectrums. maybe we can choose different categories, and show relevant research papers on the spectrum where they line up. im  thinking, like this: for a topic like "climate change" we could then allow a user to click a phase (or ask their own) like "is nuclear power worth the risk?" and rewell will show a view with different sources on a spectrum. this particular question might have the left saying not worth the risk, and the right saying worth the risk, and then research papers that are highly relevant to the question shows up along this spectrum. you can click it and then you get to the page for that source.

inside the source, you can read the source paper, and also discuss, reference parts of it and discuss in threads.

back in the topic, when asking this question,  there will be discussion threads that are relevant to your search that will appear that has people discussing. so in the source (research paper) we dont need a spectrum view or anything there. the spectrum view should be the same no matter witch way you entered into it.


im thinking, that inside of the source view, users can leave comments at different parts of the the research papers. if a user wants to leave a comment, they can click on the area of text and the discussion side bar will slide out from the right side and they can have a discussion there. this discussion will be mapped to that part of the text.i also want a visualization that shows like a histogram along the edge in the research paper reading area along the vertical edge, that  shows how much discussion has happen across the text, maybe a particullar part is controversial and sparked alot of discussions. i want to vissualize that deep or many threads exists at this part of the text.


2. im thinking, we get to a search result page, with a ai generated answer that reflect the status of research backed (kind of how perplexity works, we will use that initially). the user will also be able to ask questions and learn more (like a chatbot) and this chatbot/ai will reference which sources it uses. but we will also have relevant topics and recommended sources listed below.


when sarching i also want relevant things to appear in real time, like auto complete, like users, groups, topics etc, but if you choose not to click any of them, and just press enter, then you will get to the search result view i just mentioned.
